## üéØ Clinical Applications

### Primary Pattern & Manifestations
**Pattern**: Exterior wind-cold with disharmony between ying and wei
**Key Symptoms**: Mild fever, aversion to wind/cold, sweating, headache, nasal congestion, stiff neck and shoulders
**Tongue**: Thin white coating
**Pulse**: Floating and slow, or floating and weak

### Secondary Applications
- Chronic fatigue with exterior deficiency
- Allergic rhinitis with wind-cold pattern
- Chronic urticaria (hives) with qi deficiency
- Post-partum wind-cold syndrome
- Digestive weakness with exterior symptoms

### Modern Clinical Uses
- Common cold with sweating and aversion to wind
- Chronic fatigue syndrome with immune deficiency
- Functional digestive disorders with cold constitution
- Allergic conditions with wind-cold pattern
- Post-viral weakness and sweating

## üìù Therapeutic Actions
**Primary**: Release exterior wind-cold, harmonize ying and wei

**Secondary**: Strengthen middle jiao, regulate defensive qi, stop abnormal sweating

